parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Rotors and Drums
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Undersized rotors and excessive wear of drums can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising vehicle safety.
The weak underhood side arms can cause the hood to fall down, potentially injuring the driver or obstructing their view, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The hood falls down while driving
the hood does not stay in place
the hood is difficult to keep open
the hood suddenly closes while working under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sun visor can impair the driver's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during daytime driving.
symptoms: The sun visor does not stay in place
the sun visor obstructs the driver's view
the sun visor does not provide adequate protection from sun rays.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery terminal can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially stranding the driver. In severe cases, the battery explosion can cause physical harm and damage to the surrounding components.
symptoms: the battery terminal is loose or pulled out of the battery
the battery is swollen or damaged
there are signs of acid leakage or corrosion around the battery terminal.
